Interface ValsDelegate<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the value wrapped by the delegated property...

    public interface ValsDelegate<T>
    A context object passed to the various types of change listeners registered in property lists such as Vals and Vars. It provides helpful context information about the change, such as the previous and current value of the property, the index of the property in the list, and type of change.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • changeType

        Change changeType()
        Returns:
        The mutation type of the change which may be one of the following:
        • Change.ADD
        • Change.REMOVE
        • Change.SET
        • Change.SORT
        • Change.CLEAR
        • Change.DISTINCT
        • Change.NONE

      • index

        int index()
        Returns:
        The index at which a list mutation took place or -1 if the change does not involve a particular index, like a list clear or a list sort.

      • oldValue

        Val<T> oldValue()
        Returns:
        The previous value of the property or an empty property if the change does not involve a previous value.

      • newValue

        Val<T> newValue()
        Returns:
        The current value of the property or an empty property if the change does not involve a current value.

      • vals

        Vals<T> vals()
        Returns:
        An immutable copy of the property list after the change has been applied.
